{"title":"Bilgah","link":"/en/wol/d/r1/lp-e/1200000735","html":"<span id=\"page314\" class=\"pageNum\" data-no=\"314\" data-before-text=\"314\"></span><strong>BILGAH</strong>(Bil&#x2B9;gah) [Brightening].<strong>1. </strong>Head of the 15th of the 24 priestly service divisions when David reorganized the sanctuary service.<wbr>&#x2014;<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200000735/0/0\" data-bid=\"1-1\" class=\"b\">1Ch 24:1,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200000735/0/1\" data-bid=\"1-2\" class=\"b\"> 3,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200000735/0/2\" data-bid=\"1-3\" class=\"b\">&#xA0;14</a>.<strong>2. </strong>A priest who returned to Jerusalem with Zerubbabel in 537&#xA0;B.C.E. (<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200000735/1/0\" data-bid=\"2-1\" class=\"b\">Ne 12:1,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200000735/1/1\" data-bid=\"2-2\" class=\"b\"> 5,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200000735/1/2\" data-bid=\"2-3\" class=\"b\">&#xA0;7</a>) In the following generation the head of his paternal house was Shammua.<wbr>&#x2014;<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200000735/2/0\" data-bid=\"3-1\" class=\"b\">Ne 12:12,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200000735/2/1\" data-bid=\"3-2\" class=\"b\"> 18,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200000735/2/2\" data-bid=\"3-3\" class=\"b\">&#xA0;26</a>."}